# ── Stripe (tip jar) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Stripe config lives as Cloudflare Pages runtime env vars on the project
# (Settings → Variables and Secrets) — NOT Vite build vars, never bundled into the
# frontend JS. Set them PER-ENVIRONMENT (use the Choose Environment dropdown):
#   • Preview     → TEST keys  (pk_test_… / sk_test_…)
#   • Production  → LIVE keys  (pk_live_… / sk_live_…)
#
# Variables (same names in both environments):
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY       → add as a SECRET / encrypted.   sk_test_… or sk_live_…
#   STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY  → plain text (it is public; served to the browser by
#                             /api/stripe-config).            pk_test_… or pk_live_…
#
# Test vs live is decided by which environment is deployed — there is NO mode flag.
# The "Test mode" badge is derived automatically from the pk_test_/pk_live_ prefix.
#
# Local development (wrangler pages dev): put your TEST keys in .dev.vars (gitignored):
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx
#   STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxx
